help with morning sickness my morning sickness has started seems to last all day night i feel dreadfull from the time i get up i can't face eating anything by the time i've got up boiled the kettle i have to lie down as i feel like i'm going to pass out then it's straight to the toilet anybody got any tips or advice i never felt this bad the last time i am in the uk never heard of preggie pops or such things can we get them in the uk if so where from thanks preggie pops get a box of them or the preggie lozenges and keep them by your bed i used to work at a children's consignment shop and we couldn't keep them in stock they work so well that we had chemotherapy patients come in and buy them for their own use pop one in your mouth as soon as you wake up and do that throughout the day also some women find that keeping a box of crackers or something like that beside the bed as well eat a few crackers before you even get out of bed in the morning even if it only works for a few minutes that's a few minutes that you aren't sick best of luck edit i looked online and the website for ordering them in the uk is http www mothersbliss com you can also find them at most maternity stores i've seen them at motherhood maternity but i don't know if you have those stores where you're at either Shaggy dog story The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Social rule Time Out of Mind Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Mattress Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Ron and Fez Hypoglycemia Salad Fingers Avenue Q Elvis Presley Jackass: The Movie Breastfeeding Stomach cancer Mathematician Spidey Super Stories Cliff Richard Jon Secada Phishing Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Out-of-body experience About a Boy Baldness Blankets (graphic novel) Childbirth Tlingit Shit Fecal incontinence Customs and etiquette of Japan Urinary incontinence Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Insomnia The Doctor Dances Bon Jovi Notable lines in the St